After the collision, the car ended up running over a pedestrian, killing him at the scene. Another pedestrian sustained injuries.
The boda-boda rider died at the scene whereas his passenger sustained severe injuries.
The survivors were taken to Tenri private hospital and admitted.
Embu West police boss Charles Kinyua said the car and motorcycle were towed to the local police station for inspection.
"Road users should observe traffic rules so that we don't continue losing lives to accidents which can be prevented," he said.



